{"key":"post-9456728","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9456728</id>\n<content>If you spawn to bulk, simply wait for it to fully colonize, and then cover with the casing layer as described above.&amp;nbsp; A bulk substrate will generally give a larger harvest, but you can case grains too.&amp;nbsp;  In fact, if you spawn to bulk, you don't even need to case if you're growing cubes.&amp;nbsp; If you don't spawn to bulk, a casing layer is required because straight grains won't fruit, or will fruit poorly at best.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9456783</next>\n<prev>9456665</prev>\n<first>9456338</first>\n<last>9470739</last>\n<when>1229639475</when>\n<utime>12/19/08 12:31 AM</utime>\n</post>"}